The paper proposes a method for out-of-sample extension using Gaussian Process Regression, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of probabilistic modeling. The paper also discusses the mathematical connection between the proposed method and the Nystrom extension, which is a technique commonly used in dimensionality reduction and falls under the category of numerical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
